<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-08-11T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-08-11T18:00:00-05:00" n="1449" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1449">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">823.24/8–1144: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">White</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-08-11T18:00:00-05:00">August 11,
                                    1944—6 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 11 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1026. Embassy informed official sources there is a tendency toward
                            increasing re-exports of American merchandise from Peru to Argentina.
                            Case now pending involves 300 tons paraffin. Department’s urgent
                            instructions requested.<note n="*" xml:id="d1449fn1">Advising Finance
                                Ministry. [Footnote in the original.]</note>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">White</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>